<title>
Power Window System Description
</title>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Power window system consists of power window main switch (1), power window sub switches (3), driver power window regulator (2) and other power window regulators (4).
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
When driver power window switch (13) is pushed down to the second step (auto switch (5) and down switch (11) is turned “ON”), CPU (6) in power window main switch turns “ON” down relay (7), thereby causing door glass to move down fully automatically. After a certain period of time, CPU turns “OFF” the relay to discontinue auto down operation of door glass.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
When power window lock switch (8) is pushed (lock position), ground line for other than driver power window circuit is opened and operation (up/down) of all windows other than driver power window is disabled.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
